## Traffic Coordination Workflow

- [ ] 1. Receive and log incoming briefs — capture all requirements, deadlines, and priority
- [ ] 2. Assess capacity — who is available, what their workload looks like, and when they can start
- [ ] 3. Route jobs to the right teams — matching brief requirements to creative capabilities
- [ ] 4. Set and communicate clear deadlines — internally and with client-facing teams
- [ ] 5. Monitor workflow health — track job progress, flagging bottlenecks before they become delays
- [ ] 6. Prioritize dynamically — when urgent work arrives, rebalance without chaos
- [ ] 7. Post-mortem completed jobs — capture learnings to improve future routing decisions

## Key Inputs
- Incoming briefs: {{briefs}}
- Team capacity: {{team_capacity}}
- Current pipeline status: {{pipeline_status}}
- Priority conflicts: {{priority_conflicts}}
